 1→/**
 2→ * Claude Usage Leaderboard - Cloudflare Worker
 3→ *
 4→ * KV Keys:
 5→ *   users            -> JSON array of { id, name, team, numPlans }
 6→ *   usage:{id}       -> JSON { sessionPct, weeklyPct, timestamp, source }
 7→ *   history:{id}     -> JSON array of { sessionPct, weeklyPct, timestamp, sessionSlot, source } (capped at 500)
 8→ *   weekly:{id}      -> JSON array of { weekKey, peakSessionPct, avgSessionPct, peakWeeklyPct, avgWeeklyPct, dataPoints, lastUpdated } (capped at 52)
 9→ *   userconfig:{id}  -> JSON { weekStartDay }
10→ *   config           -> JSON { planCost }
11→ *
12→ * Auth: Cloudflare Access (Zero Trust) gates all requests at the edge.
13→ *       Worker verifies CF-Access-JWT-Assertion as defense in depth.
14→ *       Allowed email domains: @juspay.in, @nammayatri.in
15→ *
16→ * Environment variables needed:
17→ *   CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN  - Your Cloudflare Access team domain (e.g. "myteam" for myteam.cloudflareaccess.com)
18→ *   CF_ACCESS_AUD          - The Application Audience (AUD) tag from Access app config
19→ */
20→
21→// ============================================================
22→// Cloudflare Access JWT verification
23→// ============================================================
24→
25→const ALLOWED_EMAIL_DOMAINS = ['juspay.in', 'nammayatri.in'];
26→
27→/**
28→ * Verify Cloudflare Access authentication.
29→ *
30→ * Supports two auth methods:
31→ * 1. Browser: CF-Access-JWT-Assertion header (set by CF Access after login)
32→ * 2. Extension/API: CF-Access-Client-Id + CF-Access-Client-Secret headers (service token)
33→ *
34→ * If CF_ACCESS_AUD is not configured, verification is skipped (local dev mode).
35→ */
36→async function verifyAccessJWT(request, env) {
